00:00:00.530 --> 00:00:04.830
More powerful is, a correctness guarantee, in which the pre and

00:00:04.830 --> 00:00:08.850
post conditions are specified by all, for all callable operations,

00:00:08.850 --> 00:00:12.380
thus guaranteeing that the component operations successfully execute.

